    "body": "> Sounds like an interesting idea.\r\n> \r\n> Motivation-wise, can you elaborate why does this\r\n> \r\n> > Potential applications include in-browser messaging apps supporting end-to-end encryption.\r\n>\r\n> have to be coupled with Ethereum?\r\n\r\nKey distribution for e2e encryption is a hard problem.  Ethereum can solve part of the problem because it maintains a database of public key (hashes) that is widely distributed and replicated and validated.\r\n\r\nThe app is just an example; in general I think lots of apps will want a way to generate a session key that is tied to an Ethereum identity.  See also issue #130 (old but still open) which I think would be addressed by this proposal.",
